column1: % Minimum normal operating level (datum) for each reservoir is 0 Gl
% Every reservoir must have a MAX_LEVEL - maximum volume in Gl relative to datum.
% A reservoir may also have one or more contingent storage tranches below datum.
% Each contingent storage tranche has a min. level (in Gl relative to datum; a negative number) and a penalty (in $/Gl; a non-negative number).
% The min. level of a second or subsequent tranche must be below (i.e. more negative than) the min. level of the previous tranche.
% The penalty for a second or subsequent tranche must be no less than the penalty for the previous tranche.
